    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-06T07:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-06T07:29:00-05:00" n="145"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/492</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-06T16:00:00+03:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 8, 10.55 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1713. Nervousness increasing. Rumors of Bolshevik demonstration for Sunday, 9th.
                    If it materializes army less reliable than two weeks <pb facs="0256" n="182"
                        xml:id="pg_182"/> ago. Some predictions that Government go Moscow in three
                    weeks but if Bolshevik demonstrations dominate city, departure be sooner.
                    Rumanian Minister returned from headquarters says <persName corresp="#p_KGLG1"
                        >Kornilov</persName> complains that Government regulations concerning
                    restoration of [death penalty] handicap his command of situation while Minister
                    for Foreign Affairs contends <persName corresp="#p_KGLG1">Kornilov</persName>
                    given full authority under regulations approved by <persName corresp="#p_KGLG1"
                        >Kornilov</persName>. Others assert neither <persName corresp="#p_KGLG1"
                        >Kornilov</persName> nor any one able to command sufficient power to enforce
                    discipline and that German advance, if made, be unsuccessfully resisted if at
                    all. If German fleet captures Revel, as possible or probable, panic will ensue
                    here and perhaps riots.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
